Noah&#8217;s recent interview with right-wing commentator Tomi Lahren has attracted increased attention for him. NEW YORK Trevor Noah will take on the most high profile interview of his career as host of The Daily Show when he sits down with US President Barack Obama on Monday night.Obama has appeared on The Daily Show numerous times when Jon Stewart was still the host, but this will be his last late night appearance before he steps down in January.Trevor Noah will conduct the interview at the White House. The show will air on Monday night across Comedy Central and fellow Viacom networks MTV and BET, followed by tomorrow in South Africa. It s understood this will be the last time Obama makes an appearance on a late night show, with him leaving office in January.Noah s recent interview with right-wing commentator Tomi Lahren has attracted increased attention for him.